CPC International Inc saidit has completed previously-announced transactions involvingits grocery products businesses in four Asian countries withAjinomoto Co Inc &lt;AJIN.T>, raising about 300 mln dlrs.    It said it will receive about 40 mln dlrs more later,mostly this month, when closings are expected in three morecountries.  Proceeds will be used mostly for debt reduction.    CPC said Ajinomoto has purchased its equity in Knorr FoodsCo Ltd, a joint venture in Japan between the two companies,with CPC to get fees for trademark and technology use.    CPC said Ajinomoto is also purchasing 50 pct interests inCPC's wholly-owned subsidiaries in Hong Kong, Malaysia, thePhilippines, Singapore, Taiwan and Thailand. Reuter&#3;